1
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,960
<i>Lookwa insists she won't take it back.</i>

2
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:40,840
- We'll be able to reopen the case, right?
- Absolutely.

3
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:43,720
<i>You saw it, right?</i>
<i>Puth just came to visit.</i>

4
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,680
<i>There's really nothing</i>
<i>going on between us.</i>

5
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:48,160
I saw it. But I don't believe it!

6
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:51,400
PREVIOUSLY

7
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,440
Ve!

8
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:57,280
- Miss Prae!
- Prae!

9
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:59,840
<i>If you want evidence,</i>
<i>come to Singha's house.</i>

10
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:01,440
<i>Come alone.</i>

11
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:03,880
She's in here, officer. She's here.

12
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,800
Come on, Nun. Come with me. Slowly.

13
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,000
Be careful.

14
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:11,640
Come.

15
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:16,080
- What's wrong? What is it?
- Mom…

16
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:18,600
I think I took too many antidepressants.

17
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:21,240
It's okay. Walk slowly. Let's go.

18
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:28,360
- Nun, come here.
- Mom.

19
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:31,200
- Mom.
- Come here. Don't look. Don't look.

20
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:32,480
Don't look.

21
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,760
Let's go.

22
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,000
Mom.

23
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:45,840
Why… Why is Singha…

24
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:47,720
covered in blood?

25
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:50,200
What happened?

26
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,920
- I killed him.
- Huh?

27
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,160
I killed that bastard myself.

28
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,560
Mom…

29
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,400
You don't have to
be afraid of him anymore.

30
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,800
He can't hurt you ever again.

31
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:02,000
Don't be scared anymore.

32
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,920
We can't stay here.

33
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,480
We have to run, Mom. We have to run.

34
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:10,880
- We can't stay here anymore.
- Wait, Nun, listen. Listen to me.

35
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,520
Listen to me. Listen.

36
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,560
You have to stay in the car.

37
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:18,640
Don't get out, no matter what. Understand?

38
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:22,000
If anyone asks,
tell them you didn't see anything.

39
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:24,000
Say we just came back, okay?

40
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,840
Okay.

41
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:47,040
Officer, could you please check
on my son-in-law's house?

42
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,000
My daughter and I were outside.

43
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,080
A woman called yelling

44
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:53,280
that she was going to hurt him.

45
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:54,880
Yes.

46
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:57,320
And she has a criminal record,

47
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:59,600
attempted murder on me.

48
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,960
Can you come check?
I'm afraid she'd hurt my son-in-law.

49
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,440
Yes, thank you.

50
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,800
Nun? Nun!

51
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:21,240
Nun! Nun!

52
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,600
Huh?

53
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,920
Police cars?

54
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:30,200
Officer! Officer!

55
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:32,200
This way! Officer!

56
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:50,000
Why did she call me here?

57
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:05,040
She's in here, officer. She's here.

58
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,120
Mom. Mom!

59
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,960
Mom, help me! Singha's gonna…

60
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,120
- Ma'am, stop!
- No. It's not her!

61
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,360
Officer!

62
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,760
It's not her!

63
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:23,160
- Not my daughter!
- Mom. Mom!

64
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,560
- Mom, what happened? Why is Nun…?
- Nun.

65
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,360
Why are you here, Nun?!

66
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,360
- Why are you here?!
- Singha?

67
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,840
Let's go talk. Come on.

68
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,720
Nun…

69
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,040
- Let us take care of this.
- Singha's alive.

70
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:44,320
- Singha isn't…
- Nun.

71
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,000
- Mom, Singha isn't dead.
- Nun.

72
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,440
Why?

73
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,640
Why wasn't it you standing there?

74
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:56,960
Why did it have to be Nun?

75
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,440
Mom.

76
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,480
Did you call me here

77
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:06,280
to have me take the blame for her?

78
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,760
Mr. Ki.

79
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:25,520
<i>Where are you?</i>
<i>Why did you leave without telling anyone?</i>

80
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,800
I…

81
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,960
You shouldn't be alone right now.

82
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,800
Prea told me to look after you.

83
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:34,280
I'm at Singha's house.

84
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,600
I haven't gone in yet.

85
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,360
You shouldn't go in alone.

86
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:40,320
Wait for me. We'll go in together.

87
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:41,840
Okay.

88
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,520
Or maybe it wasn't Ms. Nun?

89
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,560
What are you talking about?

90
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,360
Singha!

91
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,880
Singha…

92
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:59,720
Singha… Who killed you?!

93
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:03,120
Whoever murdered my son

94
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:06,880
will have to pay. I'll make sure of it!

95
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:13,840
They're going to pay for it!

96
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,520
Singha…

97
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,360
Ms. Nunnalin is under severe stress.

98
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:25,160
Her lawyer said
she regularly uses antidepressants,

99
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,360
so she's being transferred
to the hospital.

100
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,560
Alright.

101
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:31,560
And you said Mrs. Kanisorn

102
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,080
called you to the scene?

103
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:36,200
Yes. She called, so I went there.

104
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:39,280
But Mr. Ki told me
to wait and go in together.

105
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,400
But I think

106
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:44,240
Singha was already dead
when Mrs. Sorn called.

107
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:47,840
We'll have to wait for the autopsy
to know the time of death.

108
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:50,800
Mrs. Sorn.

109
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:54,280
The police wanted to see you
for further questioning.

110
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,480
Tell them I'm not ready.

111
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,320
Ploy and Pete have gone home.

112
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,800
You should rest too.

113
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:20,320
I want to stay and hear about Prae's case,

114
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:24,160
and also Singha's and Nun's.

115
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:33,560
Nun is still in the hospital.

116
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:36,200
The doctor said

117
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,520
she overdosed on anxiety meds.

118
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,360
Will she be okay?

119
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,560
You care about her?

120
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:51,280
Even if we're nothing to each other,

121
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,200
not even related by blood,

122
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,600
I still see her as a little sister.

123
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:01,000
If she really killed Singha,

124
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,920
it must be because he hurt her
to the point she couldn't stand it.

125
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,520
So she did that.

126
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:10,040
I'm just afraid

127
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:14,080
the truth might not be
what the police think it is.

128
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:15,560
What are you trying to say?

129
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,400
Aren't you curious

130
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:21,200
where your mom disappeared to
after it happened?

131
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,280
Why hasn't she given a statement?

132
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:55,520
Don't do it, Mrs. Sorn.

133
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,000
Mom! Mom!

134
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:00,320
- Mom.
- Ugh!

135
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,720
Mom, please don't do this.

136
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:07,560
Why are you stopping me?

137
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:12,120
Everything is ruined, Ki…

138
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:20,200
Everything I did for my children
is all ruined…

139
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,240
Because of her.

140
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:30,000
It's all because of her.

141
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:34,120
You want to see me die, don't you?

142
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:38,400
Fine, I'll die right in front of you, Ve!

143
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,120
Maybe you don't know yet.

144
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,000
Nun has confessed to the police

145
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,320
that she killed Singha.

146
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:50,280
Yes, Mr. It? What did you say?

147
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:54,320
What happened?

148
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,120
Nun confessed to murdering Singha.

149
00:11:57,960 --> 00:12:00,760
They're bringing her back
for more questioning.

150
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:05,240
I didn't think
he was capable of being so cruel.

151
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:08,600
He kept hurting me worse and worse.

152
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:11,200
He threatened me…

153
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:14,400
until I couldn't take it anymore.

154
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,120
And I wanted to kill him.

155
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,640
I did it.

156
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:24,080
I killed him.

157
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:26,840
No…

158
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:28,720
Why?

159
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,240
Why?

160
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:34,080
Why would she confess?

161
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:38,720
Ki, she didn't kill him. I…

162
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,560
I did.

163
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:44,400
Ki, I'm the one who killed him. Here.

164
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:48,960
Here. I already wrote a confession letter.

165
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:52,480
I killed him, Ki.

166
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:57,720
Mom.

167
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:00,440
Even if you left this letter behind,

168
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:04,760
it doesn't mean Nun is off the hook.

169
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:10,480
She'll only be free
if you tell the police the truth

170
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,400
about what really happened to Singha.

171
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,880
You have to face the truth, Mom.

172
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:19,600
You can't run away like this.

173
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:25,320
I don't know what to do anymore, Ki.

174
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:28,160
I don't know what to do.

175
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:33,400
I've ruined everything.

176
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:38,600
- I destroyed everything, Ki…
- Face the truth.

177
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:44,160
You have to face the truth.

178
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,160
Ki, move.

179
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:54,640
Mom.

180
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,080
Get out of the way!

181
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,600
- Mr. Ki.
- I'm going to die anyway.

182
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,440
I'm going to kill her.

183
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:03,600
Stop, Mom.

184
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,480
Mrs. Sorn,

185
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:10,400
don't you know
what you should be doing for your child?

186
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,200
Don't lecture me.

187
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,760
Ki, move.

188
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:19,880
I'll kill her. Move!

189
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:22,520
I won't let you hurt Ms. Ve.

190
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,880
Even now…

191
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:32,240
you're still siding with her?

192
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:37,600
You're still standing by her side, Ki?

193
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:41,640
Huh, Ki?!

194
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:45,320
Fine, son.

195
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,720
Fine.

196
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:51,520
Then just die together, alright?

197
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,200
You wanna die with her?

198
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:00,480
If there's such thing as the next life,

199
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:07,320
I hope I'll be born as your son again.

200
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:12,560
Let that be my atonement
for disappointing you.

201
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,680
I'll take you to the police, Mom.

202
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,120
Ki…

203
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:53,080
Your daughter has already confessed
that she killed the victim.

204
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:56,000
But my daughter's blood test shows

205
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:59,000
she took an overdose of medication.

206
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,680
That must've caused her to say that.

207
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:04,360
The one who murdered Singha was me,

208
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:06,080
not my daughter.

209
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:09,280
But on the golf club
used as the murder weapon,

210
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,600
there were no fingerprints of yours.

211
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,880
I wiped them off myself.

212
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:15,560
There were no security cameras inside.

213
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:19,680
At the time, only you, the victim,
and your daughter were present.

214
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:22,760
Do you have any proof
that you were the one who killed him?

215
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:25,880
The evidence is in my dashcam.

216
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:31,720
I took my daughter to the car

217
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:34,440
right after killing Singha.

218
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:37,960
<i>Why is Singha covered in blood?</i>

219
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,760
<i>What happened?</i>

220
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,600
<i>- I killed him.</i>
<i>- Huh?</i>

221
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,680
<i>I killed that bastard myself.</i>

222
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:45,840
<i>Mom…</i>

223
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:48,800
The evidence
should be clear enough for you now

224
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:53,440
that the murderer is me, not my daughter.

225
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:09,119
This way, please.

226
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,800
Ki…

227
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,880
Are you okay?

228
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,599
Ki.

229
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:22,119
Singha died
because Mom tried to protect me.

230
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,440
I… I didn't want Mom
to get in trouble again.

231
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:28,000
But you should tell the truth.

232
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:30,240
You shouldn't lie anymore.

233
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:45,200
- Mr. Kittisak.
- What happened?

234
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:47,560
Was it true that Mrs. Kanisorn confessed

235
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:50,080
to murdering her own son-in-law?

236
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:52,720
I won't give any comments today.

237
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,520
Everything is in the official case file.

238
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:55,440
- Please move.
- Oh?

239
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:57,560
Wait, Attorney! Mr. Kittisak!

240
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:02,360
Mr. Ki, do you know why Mrs. Kanisorn

241
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:04,400
murdered Mr. Singha?

242
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,000
Was it because

243
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:08,160
he severely assaulted Ms. Nunnalin?

244
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:10,880
At this time, both Mr. Ki and Ms. Nun
have no comments for you.

245
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:14,480
What about Mr. Sajja? Has he
said anything? Have you talked to him?

246
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:16,080
What is there to talk about?

247
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,920
My son is dead.

248
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:22,360
Of course this won't end easily.

249
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:25,080
So you will also file charges?

250
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:28,920
I have to fight for justice
for my only son.

251
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:33,480
Also, the gunman who killed the reporter

252
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:35,800
confessed that Singha
was the one who ordered the hit.

253
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:37,320
Are you aware of that?

254
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,080
What are you talking about?

255
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:42,120
Before you demand justice for your son,

256
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:44,240
you should know

257
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:47,880
he committed a crime before he died.

258
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:50,680
The hitman has confessed

259
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,280
that he was hired by your son.

260
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:55,160
And that same hitman

261
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:58,120
has worked with you before.

262
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,680
The murdered reporter

263
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:03,600
had been investigating
a bribery case tied to you.

264
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:06,280
The police will be calling you in
for further questioning.

265
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:09,720
And this doesn't even include
what Singha did to Ms. Nun.

266
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:16,520
Perhaps he turned out so violent and cruel

267
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:20,040
because of how you raised him.

268
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:21,320
This bitch!

269
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:24,680
- What the hell?
- This is a police station.

270
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,080
And you still act like that?

271
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:27,400
Nun.

272
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:30,440
Are you angry
because what she said is true?

273
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:33,080
- Is it?
- You all better stop this nonsense.

274
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:35,520
Let's go.

275
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,200
So you really didn't know

276
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:46,000
Mr. Singha ordered the hit?

277
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:48,840
I know nothing,

278
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:51,600
except that my son is dead.

279
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:54,600
As for the rest, I won't answer.

280
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:56,360
- But this is all connected.
- Make way.

281
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:58,000
- Isn't it, Mr. Sajja?
- Please wait.

282
00:19:58,080 --> 00:20:00,280
- Mr. Sajja.
- Please answer, Mr. Sajja.

283
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:13,600
Here, have some warm tea.
It might help you feel better.

284
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:17,240
You shouldn't rely on those meds so much.

285
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,160
I'm sorry.

286
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:29,400
It's not just me.

287
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,440
There are many others
you should apologize to.

288
00:20:34,040 --> 00:20:35,360
I know.

289
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,840
If you know,

290
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:40,280
you shouldn't keep
running from your mistakes.

291
00:20:40,360 --> 00:20:42,320
You might think

292
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:45,400
no matter what you did wrong,
someone would protect you.

293
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:48,400
But in the end,

294
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:51,800
no one can run away from their own sins.

295
00:20:58,240 --> 00:21:00,120
I was just a coward.

296
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:02,760
I was the one

297
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,520
who let this spiral out of control.

298
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:09,080
But I've made my decision.

299
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:12,280
I'll take full responsibility

300
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:14,440
for everything I've done.

301
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:19,560
But I just want to say.

302
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,480
I'm sorry,

303
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:26,960
big sis.

304
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:38,520
Honestly,

305
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:42,840
I should've called you "sister"
a long time ago.

306
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:48,400
No matter what,

307
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:51,040
you're like a little sister to me.

308
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,040
Actually…

309
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:07,520
Ki told me who you are a while ago,

310
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:10,040
but I just didn't have
the courage to say it.

311
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:15,360
I couldn't even bring myself to say
the truth that I knew…

312
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:19,720
what Mom did to you.

313
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,400
Because

314
00:22:23,360 --> 00:22:26,600
I was partly responsible
for what happened to you.

315
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:32,600
I was the reason
you almost died in that orphanage.

316
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:35,000
What are you talking about?

317
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:38,400
<i>Mom told me</i>

318
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:40,360
<i>it was because of me</i>

319
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:43,080
<i>that she found out where you were.</i>

320
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:46,600
But I didn't know what she did to you.

321
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,960
Whatever it was, it probably wasn't good.

322
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:52,680
It was all because of me.

323
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:57,080
Ki never knew what Mom did to you

324
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:59,800
and your mom.

325
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,400
I just want you to know it.

326
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:05,600
I don't want you to misunderstand.

327
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,840
I know

328
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:10,600
Mr. Ki had nothing to do with it.

329
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,760
Even if he never said it,

330
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,240
I know

331
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:19,320
he loves you very much.

332
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:23,760
And I never said it either…

333
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:30,480
that I love him too.

334
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:49,720
Mr. Ki.

335
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:52,160
Are you done talking to Nun?

336
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:54,800
Yes.

337
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:58,200
That's why I have something to tell you.

338
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,960
Even if he never said it,

339
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:05,800
I know

340
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,920
he loves you very much.

341
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:11,760
And I never said it either…

342
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,160
that I love him too.

343
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:21,600
I want to tell you that…

344
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:23,720
I have something to tell you too.

345
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:27,520
You go first.

346
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:37,320
The divorce papers you wanted,

347
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,800
I've had my lawyer take care of it.

348
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:42,880
You'll get everything
that belongs to Liangsuttha

349
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:44,600
once the case with my mom is concluded.

350
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:46,880
I'm returning everything to you,

351
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:49,600
just like I promised.

352
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:00,720
And what were you going to tell me?

353
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:03,200
I was going to say…

354
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:07,080
When your mom's case goes to court,

355
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:11,520
I'll be telling the whole truth.

356
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:13,400
I understand.

357
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:16,400
It's time everyone faces the truth.

358
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:19,440
Mom, Nun,

359
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,040
and me.

360
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:28,440
Thank you for the divorce papers.

361
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:53,040
Dad, Mom,

362
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:57,080
I've gotten everything
that belongs to us back.

363
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:08,360
Thank you, dear.

364
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:10,920
Hathai,

365
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,520
you've been through so much, haven't you?

366
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:17,080
I was so exhausted I almost gave up.

367
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:19,440
Even now,

368
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:24,320
I couldn't even say I love him.

369
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:48,880
Ms. Nun said she isn't accepting visitors.

370
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:51,760
Did you tell her it was me?

371
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:53,520
Yes, I did.

372
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:57,000
But she insisted
she's not accepting anyone.

373
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:12,000
Then tell her I'll come back again.

374
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:13,960
I'll keep coming until I can see her.

375
00:27:14,560 --> 00:27:16,160
No matter what happens,

376
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,680
no matter what anyone says,

377
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:22,080
I still love her all the same.

378
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:56,920
Mr. Sajja only sent a lawyer
to co-prosecute with the state.

379
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:59,160
He didn't show up himself.

380
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:03,080
I think he's worried
the case involving his son

381
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:05,000
might tie back to him.

382
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:07,040
What about my case?

383
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,560
That one's serious.

384
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,720
The police opposed bail.

385
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:14,240
But don't worry.

386
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:16,640
You've confessed.

387
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:19,000
And your motive is understandable.

388
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:21,640
I'll plead for leniency.

389
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,320
You likely won't serve
more than ten years.

390
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:26,360
Ten years?

391
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:29,840
If it's that long, what's the point
of hiring such an expensive lawyer?

392
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:31,280
I understand.

393
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:33,920
But once the verdict is out,

394
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:36,920
you still have a good chance
of sentence reduction.

395
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:47,120
You know
what Aunt Sorn's plan is, don't you?

396
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,520
She's going to ask the court for mercy.

397
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:52,200
Say she did it out of vengeance
for her daughter.

398
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:54,680
To reduce the sentence, right?

399
00:28:57,080 --> 00:28:59,280
I won't let this end that easily.

400
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,240
Ki.

401
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:12,680
That night, I overdosed on anxiety meds.

402
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:14,640
My memory was fuzzy.

403
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:17,560
I barely remembered anything.

404
00:29:17,640 --> 00:29:20,920
Did you see the defendant
strike the deceased with a golf club?

405
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,320
No.

406
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:23,800
Is it true

407
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:28,480
that before the defendant acted,
the deceased had physically assaulted you

408
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,760
and insulted you repeatedly
in front of the defendant,

409
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:33,640
your mother?

410
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:35,520
Yes.

411
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:40,080
These wounds…

412
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:42,760
were caused by him.

413
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,480
No more questions.

414
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:52,360
That night,
the defendant called you, didn't she?

415
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,240
Yes.

416
00:29:53,840 --> 00:29:55,600
Can you tell us
what the conversation was about?

417
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:59,000
She called to get me
to go to the victim's house.

418
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:02,120
Because he had hired a hitman
to shoot me and my friend.

419
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:04,920
The police are already
investigating that case.

420
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:08,200
Why do you think
the defendant wanted you there?

421
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:11,160
I think the victim was already dead.

422
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:14,680
She called me to lure me there

423
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:16,520
so I'd be framed.

424
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:18,280
Objection.

425
00:30:20,080 --> 00:30:23,160
The witness's assumption
lacks credibility.

426
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:26,120
This is the autopsy report
indicating the time of death.

427
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:29,320
It closely matches
the call log to the witness.

428
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:32,440
It is possible
that the witness's assumption

429
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:33,840
is valid.

430
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:36,200
The defendant may have
intentionally killed the victim

431
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:37,840
in order to frame someone else,

432
00:30:38,760 --> 00:30:41,200
not driven by uncontrollable rage,
as claimed.

433
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:46,400
No further questions.

434
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:55,800
Is it true that the defendant and you
were previously involved in a case

435
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:58,040
where you attempted
to murder the defendant?

436
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:01,080
I was falsely accused.

437
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:03,240
Given that background,

438
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:05,240
did you use this chance

439
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:08,520
to unjustly accuse the defendant?

440
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:11,440
Objection.

441
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:14,080
The lawyer is leading
the witness too much.

442
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:16,280
But the question shows that

443
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:18,360
the witness lacks credibility

444
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:21,280
due to a prior case against the defendant.

445
00:31:21,360 --> 00:31:23,480
Then, I'd like to
call in additional witness

446
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:26,320
to prove her credibility.

447
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:27,840
Objection.

448
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:30,760
The new witness is from a different case.

449
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:33,920
The new witness
is deemed relevant to the case

450
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,200
currently being heard.

451
00:31:35,280 --> 00:31:37,840
The court allows
the introduction of this new witness.

452
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:52,000
So you're Wanvela's friend?

453
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:53,160
Yes.

454
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:55,400
I'll get straight to the point.

455
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:58,360
If you want to take Mrs. Kanisorn down,

456
00:31:58,440 --> 00:31:59,880
Ve and I will help you.

457
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:02,440
And how am I supposed
to trust the two of you?

458
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:05,960
The enemy of your enemy
becomes your friend, doesn't it?

459
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:08,360
You decide for yourself.

460
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:11,080
Between my friend and Mrs. Kanisorn,

461
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,880
who do you really need to go after?

462
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:17,560
If you can't reach me, contact Ve instead.

463
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,640
The defendant persuaded me

464
00:32:20,680 --> 00:32:22,720
that I'd get to marry his son

465
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:24,840
if I cooperated.

466
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:26,960
What did the defendant
want you to cooperate with?

467
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:29,960
To falsely accuse her daughter-in-law,

468
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:31,520
Wanvela.

469
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:34,160
So she was trying to paint the picture

470
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:36,240
that the witness seemed untrustworthy?

471
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:37,800
Yes.

472
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:40,600
The defendant asked me to frame her.

473
00:32:40,680 --> 00:32:42,360
How?

474
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:46,480
By staging a scene to make it look like
Wanvela tried to kill the defendant.

475
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:51,120
I have audio evidence of the defendant
discussing this setup.

476
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:53,240
Permission to play the audio recording.

477
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:54,400
Objection.

478
00:32:55,920 --> 00:33:00,400
The recording was obtained illegally.

479
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:03,280
It should not be admissible as evidence.

480
00:33:03,360 --> 00:33:06,800
But this is a serious case,
and this is key evidence.

481
00:33:07,320 --> 00:33:10,240
The truth deserves to be fully uncovered.

482
00:33:10,880 --> 00:33:12,360
Please consider this.

483
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:13,880
The court acknowledges

484
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:18,240
that this evidence
was unlawfully obtained.

485
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:23,120
However, in the interest of justice,

486
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:25,760
as this is a serious case

487
00:33:26,360 --> 00:33:30,240
with interrelated matters,
the court grants permission to play it.

488
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:42,000
<i>I have to get her out of the way.</i>

489
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:44,200
<i>I'll make Ki believe</i>

490
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:46,920
she tried to kill me.

491
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:48,880
Mint, I need your help.

492
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,920
What do you want me to do, Mrs. Sorn?

493
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:55,720
To make people believe
she wants to kill me,

494
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:57,040
I'll handle it.

495
00:33:58,360 --> 00:34:02,200
You just need to reveal
the evidence I prepare.

496
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:05,800
<i>And most importantly,</i>
<i>you must testify for me.</i>

497
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:09,400
Someone who would risk their own life
to frame someone else

498
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:11,280
must be cruel to the core.

499
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:14,040
When she actually does kill someone,

500
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:16,520
she still tries to blame it on others.

501
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:18,120
Too bad it didn't work this time.

502
00:34:18,199 --> 00:34:20,639
You! You framed me!

503
00:34:20,719 --> 00:34:22,360
Who framed you?

504
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:24,400
Someone like you deserves life in prison

505
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,600
or even the death penalty.

506
00:34:25,679 --> 00:34:26,719
Stop. Stop!

507
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:28,480
You're in court.

508
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:31,239
Show some respect to the judges.

509
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:32,800
Please calm down, Mrs. Sorn.

510
00:34:35,159 --> 00:34:36,800
You must stay calm.

511
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:39,320
They're using this evidence to destroy me,

512
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:42,480
making it look like I killed Singha
on purpose. How could I be calm?

513
00:34:43,560 --> 00:34:45,320
But if you don't calm down,

514
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:46,920
the court might believe their side.

515
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:51,920
We're already at an advantage.
The court will be lenient.

516
00:34:52,440 --> 00:34:54,760
Their evidence and testimony
aren't strong enough.

517
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:59,720
That's all for today's session.

518
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:05,120
After the chaos in the courtroom

519
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:08,080
during the trial of the murder
of Mr. Singha Yodanan,

520
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:10,440
the verdict
has finally been delivered today.

521
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:12,040
The defendant,

522
00:35:12,120 --> 00:35:13,680
Mrs. Kanisorn Liangsuttha…

523
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:17,120
The defendant is sentenced
to 20 years in prison.

524
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:20,360
However, due to her remorse

525
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:26,320
and cooperation in court,
the sentence is reduced by half.

526
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:30,080
The court will sentence the defendant
to ten years in prison.

527
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:47,640
Tired?

528
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:51,520
After all that effort
collecting evidence against me,

529
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:53,480
this is all you managed? Really?

530
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:57,760
You'd better watch your backs.

531
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:02,680
Wow.

532
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:16,400
Thank you.

533
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:24,280
The court has ruled.
I have to accept that.

534
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:26,480
But this isn't over.

535
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:28,480
Now I'll take over.

536
00:36:33,680 --> 00:36:36,240
So I have to wait six months to apply

537
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:38,280
for good behavior classification, right?

538
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:42,080
I think you shouldn't focus
on sentence reduction just yet.

539
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:44,480
There's something more urgent.

540
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:48,080
Miss Gingploy has filed for a retrial
into the death of Ms. Gingyok.

541
00:36:48,160 --> 00:36:51,240
She claims you poisoned her,

542
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:53,360
that it wasn't an accident.

543
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:56,320
What?

544
00:36:57,040 --> 00:36:58,600
TWO MONTHS LATER

545
00:36:58,680 --> 00:37:01,360
This is the medication
Ms. Gingyok regularly took, correct?

546
00:37:01,440 --> 00:37:05,360
Yes. I was the one
who bought that case for her.

547
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:07,800
After she died,

548
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:10,440
the defendant
had all her belongings discarded.

549
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,280
But I loved my sister very much,

550
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:15,520
so I kept everything myself

551
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:17,080
without the defendant knowing.

552
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:25,400
The defendant regularly picked up medicine
for the deceased, didn't she?

553
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:26,880
Yes.

554
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:30,400
That means the defendant
knew what the deceased was taking, right?

555
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:34,320
She absolutely did.
Every time she picked it up,

556
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:37,440
she would double-check with me

557
00:37:37,520 --> 00:37:41,200
about each medication and the schedule.

558
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:44,840
The deceased's medicine case
still had some capsules left.

559
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:47,280
They were tested.

560
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:49,920
And potassium capsules
were found mixed in.

561
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:53,640
Here.

562
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:56,240
Can you confirm

563
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:58,800
whether the hospital
prescribed potassium to the patient?

564
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:03,320
Absolutely not.
Ms. Gingyok had heart disease.

565
00:38:03,400 --> 00:38:06,880
Excess potassium in the body

566
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:09,840
can lead to hyperkalemia,

567
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:13,200
causing arrhythmia,

568
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:15,080
and in severe cases,

569
00:38:15,160 --> 00:38:16,840
cardiac arrest.

570
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:19,120
The deceased had heart problems.

571
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:21,200
She would've known this.

572
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:22,960
There's no way she'd mix potassium

573
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:25,280
into her own meds.

574
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:27,600
That leaves only the person
who picked up her meds,

575
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:30,560
someone who could've
slipped in a foreign capsule.

576
00:38:31,160 --> 00:38:32,920
I was just a mother-in-law

577
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:34,600
picking up medication for my in-law.

578
00:38:34,680 --> 00:38:36,960
I never touched anything.

579
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:38,640
Please remain calm.

580
00:38:39,280 --> 00:38:40,760
Stay calm, Mrs. Sorn.

581
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,680
In that case, I'd like to submit

582
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:45,800
the fingerprint analysis
from the pill case, which just arrived.

583
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,200
Objection.

584
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:51,400
This fingerprint evidence
was not agreed upon beforehand.

585
00:38:56,920 --> 00:38:58,840
I hadn't submitted
the prints for comparison yet.

586
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:01,480
I didn't have
Aunt Sorn's prints at the time.

587
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,560
But now that we're going to court,
please help handle it.

588
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:08,280
Sure. I'll get it tested right away.

589
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:10,280
Should be done before the testimony.

590
00:39:12,080 --> 00:39:14,280
But the report and officer just arrived,

591
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:16,040
so I need to submit it now.

592
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:17,680
The court accepts this evidence.

593
00:39:21,040 --> 00:39:23,040
Besides the deceased's fingerprints,

594
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:26,800
other prints were found on the pill case

595
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:29,160
and the capsule identified as potassium.

596
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:31,720
When compared
to the defendant's fingerprints,

597
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,760
the result…

598
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:39,760
is negative.

599
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:12,720
Your Honor.
Permission to call another witness.

600
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:14,520
Permission granted.

601
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:16,080
<i>I came here today</i>

602
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:19,320
<i>to tell you one last time</i>

603
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:22,240
<i>that I won't come see you again.</i>

604
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:23,160
Nun.

605
00:40:23,240 --> 00:40:24,680
All the assets,

606
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:28,120
including the shares in the Suttha Group,
will all belong to you.

607
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:31,080
Consider it me
fulfilling my promise to you.

608
00:40:31,160 --> 00:40:33,640
There's one more thing
I need to return to you.

609
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:35,480
NEXT EPISODE

610
00:42:07,720 --> 00:42:09,720
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
